To efficiently estimate mutual information from data generated according to Model (ref), we propose to first learn the embedded low-dimensional manifold of the joint space {{arxiv_2110_13883_FO0186||FO}} via Geodesic Forests [madhyastha:20:gf], as described subsequently in Sec (ref), and then compute the local {{arxiv_2110_13883_FO0187||FO}}NN distances from this representation. In other words, we aim to approximate the distance between two points via the length of its shortest path on the manifold, i.e. its geodesic distance.